catalog.title: Phonol Dis: Diag & Mgmt
catalog.description: Introduction to sound acquisition in typically developing children and atypically developing children who exhibit speech or phonological disorders.  Examine the major etiologies of speech disorders and coexisting conditions correlated with phonological disorders.  Case studies will introduce various aspects of a comprehensive phonological evaluation and data analyses, and current approaches to phonological remediation.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

notes.note:
SENIOR ONLY - Speech and Hearing  MAJORS - 
per instructor

catalog.title: Clin Observ & Participatn
catalog.description: Involves presentations and class discussions related to assessment and remediation of a variety of communication disorders. Minimum of twenty-five clock hours of directed observation in diagnosis and treatment of speech, language, and hearing disorders, which is required by ASHA as a prerequisite to clinical practicum.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

notes.note: Knowledge of Excel spreadsheets is recommended for this course.

catalog.title: Undergraduate Internship Progr
catalog.description: This internship program provides field experience at the undergraduate level for potential future clinicians of  speech and language pathology and possible school professionals. The intern attends at the host site under the supervision of the assigned mentor. A broad exposure to the variety of professions collaborating at the host site, and what they do is achieved. Success in fulfilling the attendance hours, supervisor's grading, and a written report submitted at the end of the semester by the intern, all contribute to the final grade. 112 hours of attendance is needed to get the three credits, and a letter grade is assigned at the end of the semester.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci
